imals, plants, soil, water, sediments, rocks, and other non-human beings and materials. Rather, people make politics through them. With this book, she highlights the aspirations, moral relations, and care practices in constant play in contestations and alliances over environmental change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHuman ecologyzTurkey. 0aWetland conservationxMoral and ethical aspectszTurkey. 0aWetland conservationxPolitical aspectszTurkey. 0aWetland conservationxSocial aspectszTurkey. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aTurkey.  aconservation.  aecology.  aenvironment.  aexpertise.  ainfrastructure.  alivelihood.  awater.  awetland.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391450 cprintz978150361385040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361541040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503615410423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503615410/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021